<i>hlǣfdige</i>). As a man's name it may have been used in mockery, or be short for occupational names such as <b>Ladyman</b>.","Polish: variant of   Lada  .","Hungarian (<b>Ládi</b>): habitational name for someone from Lád in Borsod County or Lad in Somogy County."],"variants":[{"name":"Lada","meanings":["‘tendril’ or ‘creeper’, often used in metaphors describing the slender curvature of eyebrows, arms, hair, swords, lightning, and women's bodies."]}]},{"name":"Emma","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Old French name, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, originally a short form of compound names such as   Ermintrude   containing the word <i>erm(en)</i>, <i>irm(en)</i> ‘entire’. It was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain, but its popularity in medieval England was greatly enhanced by the fact that it had been borne by the mother of Edward the Confessor, herself a Norman. In modern times, it was only in moderate use early in the 20th century but rose sharply in favour in the 1970s and has since remained perennially popular."],"variants":[]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Colchester","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from Colchester (Essex)."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":83,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":92,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":103,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Emma of Colchester was born in 1466, in Colchester, Essex, England. She married Sir Thomas Clere in 1486, in Colchester, Essex, England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 1 daughter. She died in Essex, England, and was buried in Colchester, Essex, England."},"et":{"1466–":"1466–Surnud","1462–1520":"1462–1520","1490–Male":"1490–Surnud","1500–1538":"1500–1538","1505–1538":"1505–1538","1505–1558":"1505–1558","1466–Female":"1466–Surnud","15 December 1505":"15. detsember 1505","1462":"1462","Abt 1500":"umbes 1500","1490":"1490","Abt 1505":"umbes 1505","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1500":"1500","1466":"1466","1520":"1520","1486":"1486","1549":"1549","1505":"1505","1538":"1538","Steyning, Sussex, England":"Steyning, Sussex, England","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Dedham, Colchester, Essex, England":"Dedham, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Colchester, Essex, England":"Colchester, Essex, England"},"fi":{"1466–":"1466–Kuollut","1462–1520":"1462–1520","1490–Male":"1490–Kuollut","1500–1538":"1500–1538","1505–1538":"1505–1538","1505–1558":"1505–1558","1466–Female":"1466–Kuollut","15 December 1505":"15. joulukuuta 1505","1462":"1462","Abt 1500":"n